<!DOCTYPE frameset SYSTEM "frameset.dtd">
<frameset>
    <predicate lemma="drive">
        <note>
            Frames file for 'drive' based on sentences in financial subcorpus.
            Verbnet entries nonvehicle-51.4.2, drive-11.5-1.  Other framed
            members include ride.  Comparison to ride and Chris' old frames
            file.
        </note>
        
        <roleset id="drive.01" name="drive a vehicle" vncls="51.4.2 11.5-1">
            <roles>
                <role descr="driver" n="0">
                    <vnrole vncls="11.5-1" vntheta="Agent"/>
                    <vnrole vncls="51.4.2" vntheta="Agent"/>
                </role>
                <role descr="vehicle or path" n="1">
                    <vnrole vncls="11.5-1" vntheta="Theme"/>
                    <vnrole vncls="51.4.2" vntheta="Theme"/>
                </role>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="straightforward vehicle">
                <text>
                    John drives a 1958 DeSoto.
                </text>
                <arg n="0">John</arg>
                <rel>drives</rel>
                <arg n="1">a 1958 DeSoto</arg>
            </example>
            
            <example name="somewhat idiomatic">
                <text>
                    ``The more variables that indicate risk, the more [the investor]-1 is
                    going *trace*-1 to drive a hard bargain.''
                </text>
                <arg n="0">*trace*</arg>
                <rel>drive</rel>
                <arg n="1">a hard bargain</arg>
            </example>
            
            <example name="now that's dedication">
                <inflection person="ns" tense="past" aspect="ns" voice="active" form="full"/>
                <text>
                    John drove 50 miles in the driving snow to annotate
                    predicate-argument structure. 
                </text>
                <arg n="0"        >John</arg>
                <rel              >drove</rel>
                <arg n="1"        >50 miles</arg>
                <arg n="m" f="LOC">in the driving snow</arg>
                <arg n="m" f="PNC">to annotate predicate-argument structure</arg>
            </example>
            
        </roleset>
        
        <roleset id="drive.02" name="cause to move or become" vncls="11.5-1">
            <roles>
                <role descr="driver" n="0">
                    <vnrole vncls="11.5-1" vntheta="Agent"/>
                </role>
                <role descr="thing in motion" n="1">
                    <vnrole vncls="11.5-1" vntheta="Theme"/>
                </role>
                <role descr="secondary predication on arg1" n="2"/>
            </roles>
            
            <example name="straightforward predication">
                <text>
                    In an invention that *trace* drives Verdi purists bananas,
                    Violetta lies dying in bed during the prelude, rising deliriously
                    when then she remembers the great parties she used to throw. 
                </text>
                <arg n="0">*trace*</arg>
                <arg n="M" f="RCL">that -&gt;  an invention</arg>
                <rel>drives</rel>
                <arg n="1">Verdi purists</arg>
                <arg n="2">bananas</arg>
            </example>
            
            <example name="predication as direction">
                <text>
                    Each of them contributed a section at the behest of Verdi, who
                    *trace*-1 was nearly driven *trace*-1 to his own early grave by the
                    troublesome arrangements. 
                </text>
                <arg f="ADV" n="M">nearly</arg>
                <rel>driven</rel>
                <arg n="1">*trace*</arg>
                <arg n="M" f="RCL">who -&gt;  Verdi</arg>
                <arg n="2">to his own early grave</arg>
                <arg n="0">by the troublesome arrangements</arg>
            </example>
            
            <example name="stupid stock reports">
                <text>
                    [Georgia-Pacific's $3.18 billion bid for Great Northern Nekoosa]-1
                    helped *trace*-1 drive the Dow Jones Industrial Average up 41.60
                    points, to 2645.08, in active trading. 
                </text>
                <arg n="0">*trace*</arg>
                <rel>drive</rel>
                <arg n="1">the Dow Jones Industrial Average</arg>
                <arg n="2">up 41.60 points</arg>
                <arg f="DIR" n="M">to 2645.08</arg>
            </example>
            
            <note>
                The second direction is more clearly parenthetical, so it should stay
                as an ArgM while the other is an Arg2.
            </note>
            
        </roleset>
        
        <note>
            These two senses should probably be merged.
        </note>
        
    </predicate>
</frameset>
